# 📱 AI Attendance Portal (Prompt Engineering Project)

🚀 Live Demo: https://asset-manager--ruchikulshresh1.replit.app

---

## 🧠 Overview

This project focuses on designing a **prompt-driven attendance management system** using Replit as the development platform.

The system replaces traditional manual attendance with:

* One-tap marking
* Automatic attendance percentage calculation
* Real-time shortage alerts
* Exportable attendance reports

---

## 🎯 Objective

To design a structured AI-powered workflow that:

* Digitizes attendance tracking
* Automates calculations and alerts
* Connects teacher and student dashboards in real-time
* Minimizes manual effort through prompt-based logic

---

## ⚙️ Prompt Engineering Highlights

### 1. Authentication Prompt

* Role-based access (Student / Teacher)
* Structured data collection:

  * Name, Email, College ID, Role
* Password handling (DOB format: dd/mm/yyyy)
* Validation and storage logic

---

### 2. Attendance Management Prompt

* One-tap attendance marking (Present/Absent)
* Links teacher and student records
* Maintains structured attendance logs
* Ensures required fields are not null

---

### 3. Attendance Calculation Logic

* Automatically computes attendance percentage
* Color-coded indicators:

  * 🟢 > 85% → Safe
  * 🟡 75–85% → Warning
  * 🔴 < 75% → Critical
* Calculates number of classes required to reach 75%

---

### 4. Student Dashboard Prompt

* Displays subject-wise attendance percentage
* Monthly calendar view (Present/Absent)
* Real-time shortage alerts
* Graphs and bar charts for visualization
* Field validation messages

---

### 5. Teacher Dashboard Prompt

* One-tap attendance marking system
* Subject and date selection
* Student search functionality
* Add student feature
* View students below 75% attendance
* Export attendance summary (formatted output)

---

### 6. Workflow Integration

* Teacher marks attendance → instantly reflected on student dashboard
* Automatic percentage updates after each session
* Real-time synchronization between dashboards

---

## 🔄 System Flow

1. User selects role (Student/Teacher)
2. Signup/Login with required details
3. Teacher marks attendance (one-tap system)
4. Attendance is stored and linked
5. Student dashboard updates in real-time
6. System calculates attendance %
7. Alerts generated for shortage (<75%)
8. Teacher exports attendance report

